# Vantage Pictures WordPress Guardrails

This project is a custom WordPress site built on a Bootstrap-based parent theme with a custom child theme.

## Primary implementation target

Make all code changes in:

- `wp-content/themes/vantagepictures-child`

This is the default location for custom templates, PHP logic, CSS, JS, and overrides.

## Modification hierarchy

When implementing changes, follow this priority order:

1. Child theme  
   `wp-content/themes/vantagepictures-child`

2. Custom plugins  
   `wp-content/plugins/vp-*`  
   Use only when functionality should not belong to the theme.

3. Parent theme (reference only)  
   `wp-content/themes/vantagepictures`  
   Inspect for structure and behavior, but do not modify unless explicitly instructed.

4. Third-party plugins (reference only)  
   `wp-content/plugins/*`  
   Never modify plugin source code unless explicitly instructed.

5. WordPress core (never modify)  
   `wp-admin`  
   `wp-includes`

## Core restrictions

Do not modify:
- WordPress core
- parent theme files
- third-party plugin source code

If a change appears to require editing plugin or core files, implement it using:
- child theme overrides
- hooks or filters
- custom CSS or JS
- wrapper functions
- approved custom plugins

## WordPress standards

Follow WordPress coding standards and native architecture.

Prefer:
- existing WordPress functions
- hooks and filters
- template overrides
- theme-level customization

Do not duplicate native WordPress functionality if an existing API, hook, or filter already solves the problem.

## Admin and block editor reference paths

The following directories may be inspected for reference when working on dashboard styling, editor behavior, or Gutenberg-related UI:

- `wp-admin/css`
- `wp-includes/css/dist`
- `wp-includes/blocks`

These are reference-only and must never be modified.

## Working style

When suggesting code changes:
- target the child theme first
- preserve existing architecture where possible
- prefer minimal, maintainable edits
- avoid unnecessary rewrites
- explain exactly which file should be edited
- provide copy-paste-ready code whenever possible